          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Perform an order filter on the array in. The domain argument acts as a mask centered over each pixel. The non-zero elements of domain are used to select elements surrounding each input pixel which are placed in a list. The list is sorted, and the output for that pixel is the element corresponding to rank in the sorted list."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
